Tic Tac Toe Game with Python and Tkinter
This project implements a classic Tic Tac Toe game using Python and the Tkinter library for creating graphical user interfaces. Players take turns making moves on a shared device, and the game display shows the current player’s turn and highlights winning combinations.

Features
A 3x3 game board with buttons representing each cell
Alternating turns between players (X and O)
Detection of winning combinations (rows, columns, diagonals)
Option to play again after a win or tie
Simple and intuitive GUI
How to Run
Make sure you have Python installed on your system.
Clone this repository or download the tic_tac_toe.py file.
Open a terminal or command prompt and navigate to the project directory.
Run the game by executing the following command:
python tic_tac_toe.py

Enjoy playing Tic Tac Toe!
Dependencies
Python 3.x (already included in most systems)
Tkinter (Python’s standard GUI library)
